<subSubSection lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="15.[264,1323,1838,1905]" lastBlockId="16.[264,1323,284,470]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="17" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,392,1838,1864]" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Frons and head narrowed. Ventral interfrontal seta nearly vertically below ventral fronto­orbital seta (except in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" box="[729,868,1879,1905]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="16" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simotris">
<emphasis box="[729,753,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[774,868,1879,1904]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="16">simotris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Foretarsal claws smoothly curved, without basal lobe. Abdomen of at least some species with dorsomedial membranous process (possibly a gland) posterior to tergite 6. Ovipositor elongate, densely setose (less so in 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" box="[328,461,364,389]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simotris">
<emphasis box="[328,461,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. simotris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), curved dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[264,1323,284,470]" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
Included species. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Borgmeier" authorityYear="1959" box="[548,805,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="digitalis">
<emphasis box="[548,805,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">Melaloncha digitalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" box="[833,1024,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="immaculata">
<emphasis box="[833,1024,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. immaculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis box="[1052,1207,404,429]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" box="[1052,1202,404,429]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="simotris">M. simotris</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Brown" authorityYear="2006" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Melaloncha" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="17" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocauda">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="17">M. xanthocauda</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
